summary: “You aren’t being serious are you?” Harry turned and looked at you over his shoulder with a playful smirk on his face causing...
body:
“You aren’t being serious are you?” Harry turned and looked at you over his shoulder with a playful smirk on his face causing you to just let out a groan. “When you said you wanted to spend more time together I thought you meant cuddles on the couch and dinner dates.” You mumbled as he grabbed your hand and led you across the street.

“Oh it’ll be fun love, you said you wanted to try a class.” You just rolled your eyes as he laughed when he looked over and saw the little pout on your face making the crinkle between your brows appear. Harry let go of your hand so he could open the door for you allowing you to enter the building that was too bright for your liking on the inside and filled with people who looked like they had chosen to be there unlike yourself, who was dragged here by your mischievous boyfriend who had promised you pancakes and coffee. “You’re gonna love it,” You couldn’t help but just let out a sigh of defeat when Harry placed a kiss to the top of your head as he placed his arm over your shoulder. “Promise.” He added as he made you walk towards to counter to check in.

“Hi! Welcome to Soulcycle!” You wanted to let out a groan at the woman’s cheery voice but you kept it to yourself as Harry began checking the two of you in allowing you to look around and as you saw everyone dressed in their matching workout sets it slowly it all began to click in your head.

“Before you say anythin,” Harry whispered in your ear as he wrapped his arms around your waist from behind, pulling you closer to him. “I didn’t get you these just fo this class.” His hand gave the waistband of your new workout leggings a pat making you roll your eyes as you tilted your head upwards to look at him. “I jus like the way you look in them, but they do come in handy for things like this yeah?” You just shook your head as you tried to fight off the smile that wanted to take over your face as Harry wiggled his eyebrows at you.

“Yes they come in handy when your oh so lovely boyfriend tricks you into thinking you’re going to get to sit in a comfy seat and eat your weight in breakfast foods but in reality you’re about to sit on an uncomfortable bicycle seat for an hour and sweat your ass off.” You felt Harry’s chest rumble as he laughed while nuzzling his face in the crook of your neck making you giggle as you placed your hands on top of his that were on your waist.

“Sounds like a lovely boyfriend indeed.” He mumbled into your neck before placing a sweet kiss right below your ear. “Let’s go get ready shall we pet?” He slowly unwrapped his arms from around your waist making your bottom lip poke out in a pout, Harry just chuckled as he grabbed your hand and led the way, you knew he’d been here multiple times so it came as no surprise that he knew exactly where he was going.

summary: Uh hi can you write something quick about Harry learning his girlfriend has depression and self harms, or has a history of...
question: Uh hi can you write something quick about Harry learning his girlfriend has depression and self harms, or has a history of these? Maybe kisses the marks she has on her hips or tells her things he believes about her that she doesn't see in herself? Cuddle with her in a blanket or get her chocolate or ice cream? Idk. I just ... the people surrounding me do not understand my mental health. I feel belittled and invalid. I'd like to imagine that Harry would be more caring/sensitive to me/it.
answer:
Oh gorgeous I’m so sorry that has happened. I care about you and I’m sure your family does as well and if not, it’s their lose and they’re assholes. I’m going to write something a bit closer to anxiety then depression even though anxiety comes from depression, well that’s what my doctor said. This is just because I think this is an insanely sensitive and triggering topic so I don’t want to offend anyone or you by bringing up stuff that is best left in the past or by writing it wrong. So this is mostly of me having an anxiety attack the other night and a little thing Harry could have done to help it.

Also may I add this guy jumped a rope and by passed his security to hug a girl who was crying and shaking and hugged and asked her if she was okay until she was, so he would definitely be very very caring and sensitive to it he would know the second you were feeling down and he’d just cuddle you up in his arms and press kisses to your cheek and all over your face asking what was wrong and if he could help with anything and if you didn’t want to talk he would just shrug his shoulders and be like that’s okay I’ll be here when you’re ready and just keep holding you until you felt better, his hand gently stroking through your hair and maybe he’d start to hum a song and you can feel the vibrations of it through his chest. He would definitely care love.

…

You were sat up in bed because it just felt a little easier to breathe. It was 2 am and like clock work anxiety decided to hit you and you couldn’t sleep. Your tossing and turning had woken Harry up about ten minutes ago and his hand had been massaging softly over the small of your back as he told you to breathe in and back out.

Despite his soft words it wasn’t working. Nothing ever really did when you worked yourself up this much. You couldn’t even figure out why you were so anxious, it wasn’t that big of a problem, but here you were, muscles tense, weight on your chest, struggling to breathe and tears stinging at the edge of your eyes.

“Do you want me to get you a water?” Harry asked softly.

“I don’t know.” You moaned, trying to concentrate on his touch instead of the weight pressing down on you.

Harry snuggled in closer, trying his best to wrap himself around you. “If it helps, I love you. H-”

“What?” you interrupted him, the weight quickly lifting from your chest, your breathe steadying.

The tears were still brimming in your eyes but it was for a different reason now. Harry had never said that to you before. Your eyes moved down to look at him, heart beating a little erratically as he watched you softly, his hand coming up to wipe at your tears.

“I love you YN, and I hate seeing you like this, hurts me to.”

You chuckled a little. All the anxiety had left your body at those words. You didn’t imagine him saying that to you for the first time like that but it happened and it felt perfect. In that moment it was exactly what you needed to hear to snap you from your toxic thoughts and back to him. He was a perfect and loving source in your life and sometimes through the haze you couldn’t see that but he tried his best to keep you concentrated on him and all the good that was in your life.

“I love you too, Harry.” turning you rolled down onto his chest, cupping his face in your hands and pressing your lips hard against his. “Thank you and I love you so much.”

This is just because I think this is an insanely sensitive and triggering topic so I don’t want to offend anyone or you by bringing up stuff that is best left in the past or by writing it wrong. So this is mostly of me having an anxiety attack the other night and a little thing Harry could have done to help it.

Also may I add this guy jumped a rope and by passed his security to hug a girl who was crying and shaking and hugged and asked her if she was okay until she was, so he would definitely be very very caring and sensitive to it he would know the second you were feeling down and he’d just cuddle you up in his arms and press kisses to your cheek and all over your face asking what was wrong and if he could help with anything and if you didn’t want to talk he would just shrug his shoulders and be like that’s okay I’ll be here when you’re ready and just keep holding you until you felt better, his hand gently stroking through your hair and maybe he’d start to hum a song and you can feel the vibrations of it through his chest. He would definitely care love.

summary: What would happen if harry meets “the one” before the 7 seven years?
question: What would happen if harry meets “the one” before the 7 seven years?
answer:
I genuinely believe he will meet someone that he thinks is the one before 7 years. I can see him falling for someone pretty soon that he will think he’s in love with, but will later realize that he was just wearing rose colored glasses. I think this person will pretend to be something they’re not in order to win his affections. 

I haven’t skimmed every second of Harry’s chart for the next 7 years (and I’m not going to, sorry lol), but chances are there will be a few other relationships before 7 years hits, and knowing what outer planets are going to touch on his natal placements is what told me to check 7 years out.

Predictions in astrology are based off of transits. Transits give you potentials of what can happen. Every person is born with their own individual natal chart, so what happens is while that person’s life is in their natal chart, every energy has at least two frequencies, meaning that the person still has free will within the realm of those energies and frequencies to make choices that can affect which frequency they choose to take next. Confusing, I know. 

Life is preset to an extent, but we still have free will within those preset routes. That’s why two people with very similar charts may have completely different lives. Each planet has a handful of characteristics/energies that a person can choose from to lead them where they’re going. When you get good enough at astrology, you can use a person’s past choices mixed with intuition to give a near exact prediction, or if you don’t know them, read the energies you see to the best of your abilities, but it isn’t always exact. I’m not psychic, so, and ultimately Harry’s life choices will be the determining factor.

summary: She worked her way through a cheap pack of cigarettes Hard liquor mixed with a bit of intellect And all the boys, they were...
body:
She worked her way through a cheap pack of cigarettes
Hard liquor mixed with a bit of intellect
And all the boys, they were saying they were into it
Such a pretty face, on a pretty neck

It’s New York, baby, always jacked up
Whole tunnels, foreign noses always backed up
When she’s alone, she goes home to a cactus
In a black dress, she’s such an actress

She sits beside me like a silhouette
Hard candy dripping on me ‘til my feet are wet
And now she’s all over me, it’s like I paid for it
It’s like I paid for it, I’m gonna pay for this

blog.title: keep his balls empty and his belly full
blog.description:
Patience does not mean to passively endure. It means to be farsighted enough to trust the end result of a process. It means to look at the thorn and see the rose, to look at the night and see the dawn.
Impatience means to be shortsighted as to not be able to see the outcome. The lovers of God never run out of patience, for they know that time is needed for the crescent moon to become full.
-Rumi
